==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Meroblast
<hw>Mer"o*blast</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>me`ros</grk> part + <ets>-blast</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>An ovum, as that of a mammal, only partially composed of germinal
matter, that is, consisting of both a germinal portion and an albuminous
or nutritive one; -- opposed to <contr>holoblast</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meroblastic</ent>⟦br⟧
